definition.value: An alk-2-enoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-methylbut-2-enoic acid.
A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazoline which is substituted at positions 2 and 4 by pyridin-4-yl and dibutylnitrilo groups, respectively.
